The paper is about a new architecture for semantic segmentation, which is a computer vision task. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The approach also involves a feedforward multilayer network, which suggests that it may be relevant to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper mentions exploiting statistical structure in the image and label space, which could relate to neural networks (cs.NE) and natural language processing (cs.CL).
